review:
Good Learning Place;
Work from Home; Projects never get finalized;
more stress on communication when there is not much interaction with clients;
not much onsite;
more networking for no cause;
firm initiative sometimes tries to get to your nerve;
firm hours matters a lot for year end discussion;
too much biasing between Deloitte in house employee and laterals;
too much politics and no growth within projects

1. Still the #1 in MIS an Enterprise Software business.
2. A lot of opportunities for training and self development.
3. Good benefits and compensation programs 1. Work-life balance;
2. Gradual fight for margins washes out talented individuals replacing them with average ones and as a result overall drive and motion reduction;
3. Innovative approach need to be revamped.

Great team;
A lot of oppurtunities for learning;
ACCA exams covered by the company;
Flexability A lot of work - during the busy season  January to July it is possible not to have any free time.
Low salaries 
Bad Management - the projects are not distibutated properly between the employees and some people are having more work than the others.

Many bonuses;
20% discount for a set each month;
Friendly atmosphere among employees and superiors. If you do not think you can handle working with lots of children and parents angry at the high prices do not apply for a job here.

Good perks: massage sessions in the office, fruit day, great tea and coffee, the occasional flexi time during the summer (one Friday off per month), professional support staff.
Low base salary, good performance incentives. As the review title mentions:
- weak leadership (they lack motivational skills and sometimes even people skills, professionalism, technical skills are also severely lacking);
- unrealistic expectations (top management submits unrealistic budgets to group and when they don't deliver, heads fall among sales and operational, top performers "heads" who "milked" their clients to the limit);
- speculative approach in customer relationships and lack of follow-up;
- low quality in delivery (6 out of 10 Perm consultants have no idea what they're doing and mostly wait for applicants);
- promises for raises or other benefits that don't happen or, if they do, it's often more than 1 year later;
- unaccountable management (actions taken due to their request or following their approval impact operational staff; if things go south, amnesia suddenly sets in for all managers);
- high turnover due to huge amounts of pressure.

The best reason to work at Oracle is the great poducts and great work experience at wellknown IT corporation. Good company for starters and making CV. - poor management (micromanagement,or even mobbing have to be)
- every fiscal year Territory/Clients list can be changed, no guarantee if you invest on building relationship and pipeline generation; with no discussion of budget target for new territory;
- double standards of corporate policies

Nice pantry, free food;
Great place to meet young talents from all over the world;
Salaries and benefits are good as a graduate role;
Quick and supportive visa sponsorship for those who really want to stay in the UK *I have read all the stories in the reviews of Analytics, and sadly every single incident mentioned is true. I recommend all the candidates read the piece of review titled "Analytics- the joke of jokes". That's a good example-think carefully before you decide to join.

Too much politics;
You get bullied until 1) you quit 2) you grow into the same kind of devils and then bully others;
The micromanagement there is insane: 
1) you get asked 20 questions of what exactly your sickness is if you feel sick and want to leave work at 5.30pm which is only 30 mins earlier. Of course after all that battling you will finally get some empathy at 5.45 and go home! 
2) careful with everything you write down in the chatting system and emails- they are watching. 3) let along they watch when exactly you enter and leave the office, how many minutes you have left your desk, and whenever whoever wherever of everything!
